In my last post, I started working through some examples given by Hastie et al in Elements of Statistical learning. I looked at using a linear model for classification across a randomly generated training set. In this post I&rsquo;ll use nearest neighbour methods to create a non-linear decision boundary over the same data.
Nearest neighbour algorithm There are much more learned folk than I who give good explanations of the maths behind nearest neighbours, so I won&rsquo;t spend too long on the theory.

